###############################################################################

Minefield Test Program

This simulated an agent learning how to traverse a minefield.
If the agent steps on a square with a mine, he dies and starts
over (luckily he remembers his Q-value table from his past life).

An example board is:
10 10 0 0
-----#----
####-##-##
-----#----
####-#-##-
---#---##-
-#---##---
-####--###
------#---
-#####--#-
-------#X-

In this case, the agent starts at position (0,0) and must make it
to the goal at X.

To run the program, type one of the following commands:

python game.py <level> <config>

The level files are in this directory and are numbered L1 through L7. L2
is the most complicated example.

The config files in this directory are the files that end with a .cfg
extension. Each of the config files is set up to use a different
epsilon function for the reinforcement learning algorithm.
